caption.text: This is the Niagara River down stream the from Niagara Falls and Horseshoe Falls. The whirlpool here actually flows in a COUNTERCLOCKWISE rotation for most of the day because of sheer power of the water flow. At night they reduce the amount of water flowing over the falls (to reduce erosion & share the water more evenly between the USA and Canada) at which time the earths rotation takes over and spins the whirlpool CLOCKWISE, like every other whirlpool in the Northern hemisphere, until they turn the flow back up!
